Percentage of Disease Status by Gender

ggplot(read_data, aes(x =Case_Control ,y= (..count..)/sum(..count..), fill= Gender)) + 
  geom_bar(position = "dodge", color= "Black")+  
  scale_y_continuous(labels=scales::percent)+ 
  labs(title = "Percentage of Disease Status by Gender", # Specify labels
       y= "Percentage", x= "Disease Status" )+
  geom_text(stat= "count", aes(label= scales::percent((..count..)/sum(..count..))), position = position_dodge(0.9), size=4, vjust=-0.3)+  #stack the labels on top of the bars
  theme_classic()+
  scale_fill_manual(name = "", values = c("White", "black"))

Test for Associations

fisher.test(read_data$Case_Control, read_data$Gender)
## 
##  Fisher's Exact Test for Count Data
## 
## data:  read_data$Case_Control and read_data$Gender

## alternative hypothesis: true odds ratio is not equal to 1
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  0.8074825 1.5018846

Import data to create Phyloseq Object

sampledata <- read_data
Taxonomy <- read_excel("Taxonomy_data.xlsx")
OTU <- read_excel("OTU_data.xlsx")

Matching row names in both the OTU table and taxonomy table

Taxonomy <- column_to_rownames(Taxonomy, var = "OTU_ID")
OTU <- column_to_rownames(OTU, var = "OTU_ID")
sampledata <- column_to_rownames(sampledata, var = "Sample_ID")

Changing both the OTU and the taxonomy Data frames into matrices

OTUmat <- as.matrix(OTU)
taxmat <- as.matrix(Taxonomy)

Creating the phyloseq object

OTUtable <-  otu_table(OTUmat, taxa_are_rows = TRUE)
Taxonomytable <-  tax_table(taxmat)
sampledata1 <-  sample_data(sampledata)
phseq = phyloseq(OTUtable, Taxonomytable, sampledata1)

Validating Checks

OTUtable <-  otu_table(OTUmat, taxa_are_rows = TRUE)
Taxonomytable <-  tax_table(taxmat)
sampledata1 <-  sample_data(sampledata)
phseq = phyloseq(OTUtable, Taxonomytable, sampledata1)

Perform differential abundance using DEseq2

OTUmat1 <- OTUmat+1
OTU1 = otu_table(OTUmat1, taxa_are_rows = TRUE)
phseq1 = phyloseq(OTU1, Taxonomytable, sampledata1)
ds <- phyloseq_to_deseq2(phseq1, ~ Case_Control)
## converting counts to integer mode
##   it appears that the last variable in the design formula, 'Case_Control',
##   has a factor level, 'control', which is not the reference level. we recommend
##   to use factor(...,levels=...) or relevel() to set this as the reference level
##   before proceeding. for more information, please see the 'Note on factor levels'
##   in vignette('DESeq2').
dds <- DESeq(ds)
## estimating size factors
## estimating dispersions
## gene-wise dispersion estimates
## mean-dispersion relationship

##    function: y = a/x + b, and a local regression fit was automatically substituted.
##    specify fitType='local' or 'mean' to avoid this message next time.
## final dispersion estimates
## fitting model and testing
## -- replacing outliers and refitting for 991 genes

## estimating dispersions
## fitting model and testing

deseq.results <- as.data.frame(res)
deseq.results%>% arrange(log2FoldChange, padj)
